Review for BRUNCH only.  I am ashamed to say that while I am still fairly new to this neighborhood, 4 solid months passed before I even considered stepping foot into Rocco's. Let me first say that I am not a huge fan of Mexican food. Rather, I am a fake Mexican food-eater (basically the only thing I will eat is a chicken quesadilla.) Also, it was because every time I walk by on my way home, the place is PACKED and LOUD. Don't get me wrong, I'm not hating, but sometimes you're just not in the ~mood~ for that vibe.  In any event, stopped in for their bottomless brunch on a Saturday. I was shocked to see that the place was relatively empty/quiet. Turns out their brunch crew is not as lively as their after-work crew. Also turns out they don't have quesadillas on their brunch menu. Honestly I was pretty bummed, but the bartender told me they would be happy to make me one and that quesadillas are not a "popular brunch option", hence they are not on the brunch menu.  Food portions were large and tasty, mimosas were great and in true fashion, bottomless. Be sure to check into yelp while you're there so you can get your free tequila shot. PSA: FREE TEQUILA SHOTS WITH CHECK IN.
